{"id": "ChIJMRSMhSHGwoAR5UrfQ8NW9Qo", "rating": 4.6, "priceLevel": "PRICE_LEVEL_INEXPENSIVE", "userRatingCount": 1816, "displayName": {"text": "PIZZANISTA! DTLA Arts District", "languageCode": "en"}, "editorialSummary": {"text": "New York-style thin-crust pizza made with artisanal toppings in an edgy, rehabbed old building.", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJMRSMhSHGwoAR5UrfQ8NW9Qo/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21wdmFGTjRTUzFXVVRWT1ZFdFFUR1ZzY1hkRFIzYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Kinda pricey for pizza. But good to come check it out for a date or cheat day. They have $1 cold 1 day old pizza slices. Gluten free options and fancy fountain drinks. Got 6 pizzas. Garlic knots and 2 diet cokes cost be about $50. I wish the pizza was softer but it was crunchy. Also got the Mac and cheese pizza. They have a free parking lot right next door. You might miss it if you drive too fast. You might actually miss the whole pizza place tbh.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Kinda pricey for pizza. But good to come check it out for a date or cheat day. They have $1 cold 1 day old pizza slices. Gluten free options and fancy fountain drinks. Got 6 pizzas. Garlic knots and 2 diet cokes cost be about $50. I wish the pizza was softer but it was crunchy. Also got the Mac and cheese pizza. They have a free parking lot right next door. You might miss it if you drive too fast. You might actually miss the whole pizza place tbh.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Bob Fang", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101565468675738341653/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIXKkvOyo_rwj-etOvfQeZcAoQDjp6CiwI3jpiL-Y-bW_NkSzs=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2026-02-27T07:48:41.223642273Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21wdmFGTjRTUzFXVVRWT1ZFdFFUR1ZzY1hkRFIzYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21wdmFGTjRTUzFXVVRWT1ZFdFFUR1ZzY1hkRFIzYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c621858c1431:0xaf556c343df4ae5"}, {"name": "places/ChIJMRSMhSHGwoAR5UrfQ8NW9Qo/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tGaGJraDFUMm8zZFV0UmNYUnRjMWxRV1RrdE4wRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "I’ve traveled all over the world and eaten pizza everywhere imaginable — Italy, France, New York, Chicago, all over Southern California. And yeah, New York has legendary spots, Chicago had some decent pies too, but I’m telling you right now… nothing compares to Pizzanista!.\n\nThis place is straight-up one of the OG pizza spots in Los Angeles and hands down one of the best pizzas I’ve ever had in my life. Ever since I was a kid, I’ve been obsessed with pizza. Back when I was surfing nonstop up and down the California coast, I’d hit different pizza joints after sessions almost every day. I’m talking pizza 4–5 times a week for years. So yeah, I know my pies.\n\nThe crust, the flavor, the sauce, the balance — Pizzanista just hits different. It’s one of those spots that stays burned into your memory because it’s that damn good. You can debate all day about the “best pizza,” but for me, this spot still sits at the top.\n\nIf you haven’t been yet, do yourself a favor and go check it out. LA is lucky to have a spot like this.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I’ve traveled all over the world and eaten pizza everywhere imaginable — Italy, France, New York, Chicago, all over Southern California. And yeah, New York has legendary spots, Chicago had some decent pies too, but I’m telling you right now… nothing compares to Pizzanista!.\n\nThis place is straight-up one of the OG pizza spots in Los Angeles and hands down one of the best pizzas I’ve ever had in my life. Ever since I was a kid, I’ve been obsessed with pizza. Back when I was surfing nonstop up and down the California coast, I’d hit different pizza joints after sessions almost every day. I’m talking pizza 4–5 times a week for years. So yeah, I know my pies.\n\nThe crust, the flavor, the sauce, the balance — Pizzanista just hits different. It’s one of those spots that stays burned into your memory because it’s that damn good. You can debate all day about the “best pizza,” but for me, this spot still sits at the top.\n\nIf you haven’t been yet, do yourself a favor and go check it out. LA is lucky to have a spot like this.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Gabe Sanchez", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106826320974771252925/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWt7TiTRVslN6lZdQFTWEB9TMKEVBSk6UeQyGCaXbfyrQc8fDc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-19T20:08:20.253984078Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tGaGJraDFUMm8zZFV0UmNYUnRjMWxRV1RrdE4wRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tGaGJraDFUMm8zZFV0UmNYUnRjMWxRV1RrdE4wRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c621858c1431:0xaf556c343df4ae5"}, {"name": "places/ChIJMRSMhSHGwoAR5UrfQ8NW9Qo/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT201NlpuYzBTbXhoT1VvdFRGbFFTekI1ZEVGUFpGRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "This was our first time visiting, and since it’s a place that so many people seem to go to, we decided to give it a try. We ordered a 12-inch pizza and a salad.\nThe salad was pretty good and enjoyable, but the pizza was very thin and quite crispy. For my personal taste, the texture felt a bit too hard—almost like it was slightly overcooked.\nIt looked like most people were ordering slice by slice rather than whole pies, which makes sense for the area. As for the price, it was reasonable considering it’s located in Downtown. Overall, it was a decent experience, though the pizza texture just wasn’t quite my style.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "This was our first time visiting, and since it’s a place that so many people seem to go to, we decided to give it a try. We ordered a 12-inch pizza and a salad.\nThe salad was pretty good and enjoyable, but the pizza was very thin and quite crispy. For my personal taste, the texture felt a bit too hard—almost like it was slightly overcooked.\nIt looked like most people were ordering slice by slice rather than whole pies, which makes sense for the area. As for the price, it was reasonable considering it’s located in Downtown. Overall, it was a decent experience, though the pizza texture just wasn’t quite my style.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Douglas Shin", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107572007472804734737/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiI-tkTAQYVhYG7XEqcEQxjAtAEy0bStWNwGj4YISzxmHE6BoUrA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2026-01-21T09:27:59.578098404Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT201NlpuYzBTbXhoT1VvdFRGbFFTekI1ZEVGUFpGRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT201NlpuYzBTbXhoT1VvdFRGbFFTekI1ZEVGUFpGRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c621858c1431:0xaf556c343df4ae5"}, {"name": "places/ChIJMRSMhSHGwoAR5UrfQ8NW9Qo/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25oUlRFNHpTMjB3VkRSMFRWOHlNaTFuY1dSa2JVRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Great New York–style pizza with amazing flavor. The cheese and crust were really good and hit that classic NYC style. The only small downside was that the dough was a bit dry, likely because I grabbed slices from the counter — I’m sure a fresh slice would be even better.\n\nService was fast and friendly, the place was clean, and overall it was a great experience. Definitely worth checking out!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Great New York–style pizza with amazing flavor. The cheese and crust were really good and hit that classic NYC style. The only small downside was that the dough was a bit dry, likely because I grabbed slices from the counter — I’m sure a fresh slice would be even better.\n\nService was fast and friendly, the place was clean, and overall it was a great experience. Definitely worth checking out!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Jude B", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111428137091585008624/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIy_5S05FnKNNXcIG1wUyShXodAkX7MZweGOJ6nqYlONzoFAA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2025-12-31T22:46:33.422910420Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25oUlRFNHpTMjB3VkRSMFRWOHlNaTFuY1dSa2JVRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25oUlRFNHpTMjB3VkRSMFRWOHlNaTFuY1dSa2JVRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c621858c1431:0xaf556c343df4ae5"}, {"name": "places/ChIJMRSMhSHGwoAR5UrfQ8NW9Qo/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xwMVRUSjFTREZtUVhaclgwRjViVmx4TkdKSFlXYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Pizzanista! Was really great! Pizza is my favorite food so whenever I'm in a new area or see a pizza joint I've never been to I will try to order from there. This restaurant was definitely a 5 star restaurant. New York style pizza with lots of flavor. It was thin, not too greasy and just enough sauce. The fountain drinks were really cool too. Not the traditional brand sodas they have everywhere.  The restaurant is cozy but they have several booths. The staff was welcoming and friendly. They were busy being it was Saturday night but they still made it a point to greet each costumer. I'm not in DTLA often but now I have a reason to go.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Pizzanista! Was really great! Pizza is my favorite food so whenever I'm in a new area or see a pizza joint I've never been to I will try to order from there. This restaurant was definitely a 5 star restaurant. New York style pizza with lots of flavor. It was thin, not too greasy and just enough sauce. The fountain drinks were really cool too. Not the traditional brand sodas they have everywhere.  The restaurant is cozy but they have several booths. The staff was welcoming and friendly. They were busy being it was Saturday night but they still made it a point to greet each costumer. I'm not in DTLA often but now I have a reason to go.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Meri meri Quite contrary", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108831266834028254353/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmwQSKlUYARgchLC2SVdo6e4-DkRAPy8TRTm3FKeOHoE4d7tw4qg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-01-26T13:58:32.897510113Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xwMVRUSjFTREZtUVhaclgwRjViVmx4TkdKSFlXYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xwMVRUSjFTREZtUVhaclgwRjViVmx4TkdKSFlXYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c621858c1431:0xaf556c343df4ae5"}], "photos": [{"name": "places/ChIJMRSMhSHGwoAR5UrfQ8NW9Qo/photos/AWCwydgHJRmEbRXjR343NAPiH1RaGrFAFTbMavWYHF9Zcn3T-1F9QsjU60FiE6U_pQA9UcEgbshgLaltWr1WVXGJfKhlAIrN3q7x1vRmjA6_wL4GcKp1ETk86ngk2FqZadjpTDH9AJPRGgn1l8hTm-EZz9IHkk2Wf3xos-4Esy_sRqGkfYLYgTGtWryLGRv0KGpmudofmWloJ_I9a26ZzqTlHepGFZ9LbmLWGZuSGZTWYpSjQBOSz6JG13aJUtIMx7mq2o5V4aa4xYLo9CjVOO7p73wBLS_pYE1US_-2SEtmSTBFLWrlDX9F2gUlDNAzqgYDXRJlBJCebs2usqnD0oXHcICEiQDTAxdHDYoDjlChxWUCyepi94k_2NoOmnKcLYQW0KtQhpeKA-VxDYhA40Hx56T_S_Aw7iFAknjuVANeZRUSZ3I", "widthPx": 828, "heightPx": 466, "authorAttributions": [{"displayName": "PIZZAN